  "summary": "Spring Security has Potential Security Misconfiguration when Using withIssuerLocation",
  "details": "Vulnerability in Spring Spring Security. When an application configures JWT decoding with\u00a0NimbusJwtDecoder\u00a0 or\u00a0NimbusReactiveJwtDecoder, it must configure an\u00a0OAuth2TokenValidator<Jwt>\u00a0separately, for example by calling\u00a0setJwtValidator. This issue affects Spring Security: from 6.3.0 through 6.3.14, from 6.4.0 through 6.4.14, from 6.5.0 through 6.5.9, from 7.0.0 through 7.0.4.",
